CSHHMAN1.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Cache Utility Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+  The%Cache Utility+dialog will display the current status of selected
   DASD caching controllers.  It allows a storage administrator to easily
   update the caching status of a controller and/or devices.  It also
   allows the administrator to view counts, status, and pinned data reports.

   This dialog gathers its data from the output of LISTDATA and SETCACHE
   commands. It displays a table with a row for each controller that was
   found during the process of filtering volumes or address ranges.
   Standard PFkeys are used to scroll up and down.

   The modifiable fields are for subsystem cache status, SD cache status,
   and NVS.  The valid values for these fields are%ON+or%YES+,%OFF+or%NO+.
  %To modify these statuses you just key over the existing status;+no
   line command operator is required.

   Valid primary commands are:
   %SORT+    UNIT, MEM or CACHE, SSID, NVS,   A scending or D escending
   %DCACHE+  Display status of all cached volumes for this system.
   %EXCEPT+  Display controllers with exceptionsal conditions from selected.
   %MEMBER+  Display a panel for modifying an existing selection group member.
   %NEW+     Display changed and new features for this release.
                             (continued)
)PROC
  &ZCONT=CSHHMN11
)END

CSHHMAN2.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Cache Utility Selection Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Cache Utility Selection+panel allows you to filter the volsers or
   range of addresses that will be included in the displayed panel.

   You must select either a VOLUME, a Group (defined by the user) or a
   RANGE of addresses.  You cannot select from more than one category.

   If you select by%VOLUME+you can enter a full or partial volser and any
   volumes that match will be included in the table that will be created.
   (for example a partial name of VOL  would select volsers like VOL001,
    VOL002, etc)

   If you select by%GROUP+ only those controllers that match ones in the
   group will be displayed on the controller panel.  A GROUP is defined
   from any controller panel by selecting controllers with an M action.
   Existing GROUP members may be modified by typing MEMBER on the command
   line.

   If you select by%address range+any online UCB address that is included
   in this range will be included in the table that will be created.
)END

CSHHMAN3.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
 ! TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(YELLOW)
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Cache Utility Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+  The%Cache Utility+dialog Device panel displays all dasd controlled by the
   selected controller. From this panel you may change the caching status of an
   individual device as well as get reports for individual devices.

   The modifiable fields are for hardware cache status, and DFW status.
   To modify these statuses you just key over the existing status; no
   line command operator is required.
   The valid values for these fields are%ON+or%YES+,%OFF+or%NO+.
   Valid primary commands are:
   %DCACHE+  Display status of all cached volumes for this system.
   %EXCEPT+  Display controllers with exceptionsal conditions from selected.
   %MEMBER+  Display a panel for modifying an existing selection group member.
   %NEW+     Display changed and new features for this release.

   Valid line command operators are set on the OPTION panel by each user.
   !Z+    browses the unformatted output of a LISTDATA COUNTS DEVICE.
   !Z+    browses the unformatted output of a LISTDATA PINNEDDATA DEVICE.
   !Z+    browses the unformatted output of a LISTDATA STATUS SUBSYSTEM.
   !Z+    displays the panel to control duplex (dual copy) operations.
   !Z+    will display a popup window to invoke Cache Performance Statistics.
   %=+    will apply the same modifications that were made to the previously
          changed row.
)INIT
 .ZVARS = '(CACHDCNT,CACHDPIN,CACHDSUB,CACHDDUP,CACHSRAT)'
)END

CSHHMAN4.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
 ! TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(HIGH) COLOR(YELLOW)
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Cache Utility Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Cache Utility+dialog Duplex panel displays all options available
   for controlling duplex (dual copy) operations.  Since some of these
   operations can involve the copying of an entire volume of data, the
   option to invoke the operation as a batch job is available.  This will
   prevent the terminal from being 'locked' while the operation is in
   progress.

   Any non-blank character can be used to select an operation.
   Field level help is available for most fields.  Place the cursor in a
   field and press the PF1 key.  A help panel will be displayed for the
   corresponding field.
)END

CSHHMAN5.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Cache Performance Stat Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Cache Performance Statistic+panel displays the output of cache
   performance over the interval that you specified.

   The only two valid actions from this panel are to press the:
    Enter key      which starts another interval to calculate performance.
      or
    PF3/15 key     which returns to the controller display panel.

   The interval may vary from what you entered depending on when the
   Enter key is pressed.  While waiting for the interval to complete the
   TSO userid is swapped out and is NOT consuming CPU resources.

   Field level help is available.  Position the cursor over one of the field
   values and press PF1 to display help for that field.

)END

CSHHMAN6.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Display Cache Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Display Cache+panel displays the status of all devices on cacheing
   controllers in a grid format. This panel is for informational purposes
   only.  No additional functions can be performed on the values on this
   panel.

   Each device will be represented by three values.  They correspond to
   the:
        device cache status    (Y for on, N for off)
        device DFW status
        device duplex status   (N not duplexed, P primary, S secondary)

   A value of ... indicates the volume is offline or not defined.
)END

CSHHMAN7.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Exception Panel Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Exception+panel displays the reason that a controller is considered
   to be in an exceptional state.  This panel will be displayed automatically
   if the user has specified so on the OPT panel.

   Only the controllers that pass the initial selection filtering will be
   checked for exceptions.  The user can modify the CACHXCPT exec to
   add or delete other exceptional conditions that they want checked.

   These conditions are considered exceptions:
     Subsystem cache is OFF
     NVS is in a disabled state (neither ON or OFF)
     This controller has memory offline
     This controller has pinned data

)END

CSHHMAN8.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Selection Group Panel Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Selection+panel displays a list of controllers you have selected for
   inclusion in this selection group.  Selection groups are used to 'filter'
   which controllers will appear on the controller panel.

   On this panel you may enter a comment to describe each controller for
   future reference.  You may also update the other fields.  To save or
   replace a group, enter the member name you wish to use for this group and
   press the ENTER key.  If you choose not to save the member enter CANCEL
   in the command area of press the PF3 key.
)END

CSHHMAN9.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Selection Group Panel Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Selection+panel displays a member list of selection groups.  You
   select one member from this list and press PF3.  The selected member is
   now displayed for modification on the selection group panel.

   You may delete existing lines by entering D on each line to be deleted.
   You may add new lines by entering A or I on any line.
   You may update information on any line by typing over the displayed data.
   Updates will be made each time you press the ENTER key.  When you are
   finished modifying this member press the PF3 key to return to the controller
   panel.
)END

CSHHMN11.text:
)ATTR

)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Cache Utility Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   Valid line command operators are set on the OPTION panel by each user.

   !Z+    browses the unformatted output of a LISTDATA STATUS SUBSYSTEM.
   !Z+    browses the unformatted output of a LISTDATA COUNTS SUBSYSTEM.
   !Z+    displays a panel with all online devices and statuses listed
          for both the hardware and the SMS control blocks. Further

          help panel for that screen.

   %=+    will apply the same modifications that were made to the previously

   not 0, a popup window will be displayed that will contain the output
   that was generated by the command.

CSHHOPT.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Cache Utility Option Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Cache Utility Option+panel allows you to control whether to create
   a log file for a simple audit trail and whether to display the output
   of each LISTDATA or SETCACHE command in a popup window.

   You may also specify the values for Line commands for both the Controller
   panel and the Device panel.

   You can specify which PFKEY to press to 'refresh' the information of the
   current display.  The previous setting of the PFKEY is saved and restored
   upon exiting this dialog.

   The first time this dialog is invoked this options panel will be displayed
   with default action abbreviations.  You can reset these values to either a
   YES or NO value.  The values will be stored in a application profile.
   You can also change the values at other times by typing%OPT+on the
   command line.

)END

CSHHPERF.text:
)ATTR
 /*  (C) COPYRIGHT AMDAHL CORPORATION  1995. All Rights Reserved    */
)BODY EXPAND(\\)
+\-\%Amdahl Cache Performance Stat Help+\-\
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                                             +
+                                                                              +
   The%Cache Performance Statistic+panel allows you to collect statistics
   of cache performance from a storage controller.  You will specify the
   length of each sample interval in seconds.  The delta between the
   values collected from two LISTDATA COUNTS reports are used to determine
   cache performance.

   For 'realtime' monitoring you should specify 'F' to execute this in your
   current TSO session.  To monitor for longer periods of time or to not
   reserve your TSO session you should specify 'B' in the mode field to
   submit a Batch TSO job.  The report output will appear in the SYSTSPRT
   DD of the batch job.

   For batch jobs you must also enter the number of intervals (reports)
   that you want.  For example   an interval of 900 secs and 4 intervals
   would create 4 reports of 15 minutes each.

)END
